  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions intended to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nExact legal definitions depend on specific national and international laws.",
